Microsoft shipped one of its largest Patch Tuesdays in October — fixing ~170 CVEs including multiple zero-days that were already being exploited. - CISA issued an emergency directive after F5 confirmed a nation-state style breach and source-code/exploit data for BIG-IP was exposed. - A high-volume extortion campaign linked to the CL0P brand targeted corporate executives, claiming to have stolen Oracle E-Business Suite data and demanding large ransoms. - A critical 13-year-old Redis bug dubbed “RediShell” (CVE-2025-49844) was disclosed and patched after researchers showed Lua-sandbox escape / RCE risk. - Analysts said the August cyberattack on Jaguar Land Rover had ripple effects through October, with estimated UK economic losses reported around £1.9bn. - The UK Information Commissioner fined outsourcing firm Capita £14m in October for failings tied to a 2023 data breach that exposed millions of records. - Two high-severity 7-Zip flaws were disclosed in early October; users were urged to update immediately after researchers showed archive extraction could lead to arbitrary file overwrite/RCE. - Reports flagged a record surge in software-supply-chain attacks in October, worsening concerns about dependencies and third-party risk. - Several U.S. county/municipal systems (Kaufman County TX, La Vergne TN, DeKalb County IN and others) suffered disruptive incidents in October, highlighting continued risk to local services. - Japan’s Asahi Group acknowledged disruption after a ransomware actor (Qilin) claimed to have stolen internal files — the incident was widely reported in early October.
